Title: Dan Barker | God does NOT exist
Descript: Dan Barker gives his argument against the existence of God.SUBSCRIBE for more speakers  http://is.gd/OxfordUnionFacebook @ http://fb.me/theoxfordunionTwitter @ http://www.twitter.com/OxfordUnionOxford Union Website @ http://www.oxford-union.org/Dan Barker says that he used to be a firm believer in the gospel. He was evangelical. He tells of parables and fables whose story is meant to be fictional but the moral tale is what matters. He goes on to highlight that modern day Christians understand the use of metaphors in the Bible that everything should not be taken as pure gospel, but says where do we draw the line between what is real and what is myth?Following this he states there is no hard evidence for god, that some tales in the bible can be questioned with simple logic. Also religions become secular over time, disagreeing on minor aspects within the larger body of the religion itself.Filmed on Thursday 8th November 2012ABOUT DAN BARKER:Co-President of Freedom From Religion Foundation, and co-host of Freethought Radio.ABOUT THE OXFORD UNION SOCIETY: The Union is the world's most prestigious debating society, with an unparalleled reputation for bringing international guests and speakers to Oxford. Title: Ivar Giaever, ASME Nancy DeLoye Fitzroy and Roland V. Fitzroy Medal, 2018
Descript: Ivar Giaever, Ph.D., who shared a Nobel Prize in Physics for experimental work in superconductor tunneling, is chief technology officer at Applied BioPhysics, Inc. in Troy, N.Y. He is recognized for innovative experimental work that led to a major advance in the understanding of superconductivity and to new scientific instruments. The Nancy DeLoye Fitzroy and Roland V. Fitzroy Medal, established in 2011, recognizes pioneering contributions to the frontiers of engineering that have led to a breakthrough in existing technology, or to new applications or new areas of engineering endeavor.Dr. Giaever earned a mechanical engineering degree from the Norwegian Institute of Technology before immigrating to Canada. He worked briefly at Canadian General Electric in Peterborough before moving to the U.S. to join GE in Schenectady, N.Y. After completing the company<U+0092>s engineering program, he was with General Electric Research Laboratory from 1958 to 1988.At GE, Dr. Giaever did research on superconductivity and electron tunneling while pursuing his doctorate in theoretical physics part time at Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute in Troy, N.Y.  In 1965 he was awarded the Oliver E. Buckley Condensed Matter Physics Prize, and he was honored with a share of the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1973 for his efforts on tunneling and superconductivity.In 1988 Dr. Giaever joined the faculty at RPI and was institute professor until 2004. He and Dr. Charles R. Keese formed Applied BioPhysics in 1991 to develop, commercialize and market ECIS<U+0099>, an electric cell-substrate impedance sensing technology they had invented while at GE, and other biophysical technologies. Video profile produced and written by Roger Torda and edited by Juan Yepes.© The copyright of this program is owned by The American Society of Mechanical Engineers.

Title: Milton Friedman Schools Young Idealist - 2 (Stanford)
Descript: In this archival Free To Choose Network footage, Milton Friedman takes Q & A at Stanford University. The classic exchange might as well have taken place yesterday. The young man's questions get to the heart of tension between the values of liberty and equality -- a tension that is still with us. Friedman dissolves egalitarianism by pointing out a simple fact: wealth redistribution creates state power elites, not equality. That was the great wisdom of the founding fathers of this country, of the people who wrote the Constitution. That constitution was designed to limit government<U+0092>s powers in order to preserve the freedom of the individual, and what has happened in the past fifty years is that the fundamental character of the Constitution has really been changed. About TEDx, x = independently organized eventIn the spirit of ideas worth spreading, TEDx is a program of local, self-organized events that bring people together to share a TED-like experience. At a TEDx event, TEDTalks video and live speakers combine to spark deep discussion and connection in a small group. These local, self-organized events are branded TEDx, where x = independently organized TED event. Title: Donald Trump interview 1980 (Rona Barrett) [Reelin' In The Years Archives]
Descript: We are posting this 4 minute interview excerpt of a 34-year-old Donald Trump from October 6th, 1980, not for positive or negative political reasons but rather from an historical standpoint. We are in the business of licensing footage and that<U+0092>s why our web site is across the screen (to protect it from being used without our permission) . We realize that Donald Trump<U+0092>s presidency causes very strong emotions (both pro and con) but we are not in any way sharing this to take a side. We very much appreciate history and this is a fascinating interview considering that when our client Rona Barrett asked him these questions in 1980 he seemed to have no political aspirations, and now here in 2017, he<U+0092>s days away from becoming President.  Rona had not planned on asking him these political questions as she was there to interview him for a TV special on millionaires, but only a few minutes of the 47 minutes filmed ever aired, but nothing concerning politics.  We posted this interview for what it is, an historical document. We<U+0092>re hoping (but realize it<U+0092>s a long shot) that people will show restraint and keep the comments civil. We as archivists appreciate footage and the story it can tell about a moment in time. Over the last few decades, we<U+0092>ve dedicated so much time, money and resources to build a company that  locates, preserves and makes available for licensing, lost archival footage whether it be music performances or interviews with important figures in Film and Television, Comedy, Literature, Art, Science, Fashion, Sports and in the case of this unique interview with Donald Trump, politics.   Reelin<U+0092> In The Years Productions

Title: Donald Trump Teases a President Bid During a 1988 Oprah Show | The Oprah Winfrey Show | OWN
Descript: Donald Trump is perhaps best known for the money he's made (and lost) in real estate, his less-than-humble demeanor and his hit reality TV show, 'The Apprentice'. In recent years, the business tycoon has also been chasing the dream of holding the highest office in the land. Although many people know he has been eyeing the Oval Office for a couple of election cycles, you may be surprised to learn just how far back his presidential aspirations reach. Watch as Donald, in a 1988 appearance on 'The Oprah Winfrey Show', shares his thoughts on running for office. Title: How Did Head Colds Lead to Mutiny on Apollo 7?
Descript: The Apollo 7 crew somewhat infamously fought with mission control during their 11-day mission. It wasn't the greatest situation. A crew flying a new spacecraft a year and a half after losing three colleagues in the Apollo 1 fire already feels overloaded by their schedule when head colds hit. High tensions didn't stop the mission from being a technical success, but the personality clashes did take their toll on the flight and the astronauts' careers. For more on the Apollo 7 mutiny story, check out this article on Discovery News: http://news.discovery.com/space/histo...Apollo 7 was commander Wally Schirra's third spaceflight, making him the only man to have flown all three Apollo-era programs. More on Schirra, his career, and the impact of Apollo 7 on Vintage Space: http://www.popsci.com/blog-network/vi...For a little more background, here's the story of how Donn Eisele ended up on the Apollo 7 crew: http://www.popsci.com/blog-network/vi...And another fun tidbit: How Donn Eisele became known as \whatshisname\" among the crew! http://www.popsci.com/blog-network/vi...Want more Vintage Space? Check out the blog on Popular Science: http://www.popsci.com/blog-network/vi...And for a little Vintage Space every day, follow me on Facebook, Instagram, Google+, and Twitter as @astVintageSpace."
